<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-11174] org.apache.cassandra.metrics:type=Streaming,name=ActiveOutboundStreams is always zero</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-11174</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;org.apache.cassandra.metrics:type=Streaming,name=TotalIncomingBytes&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;org.apache.cassandra.metrics:type=Streaming,name=TotalOutgoingBytes&lt;/tt&gt; work fine but &lt;tt&gt;org.apache.cassandra.metrics:type=Streaming,name=ActiveOutboundStreams&lt;/tt&gt; is always 0.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;C* 2.1.12, Debian Wheezy&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
        <key id="12939764">CASSANDRA-11174</key>
            <summary>org.apache.cassandra.metrics:type=Streaming,name=ActiveOutboundStreams is always zero</summary>
